definitions.definition: (a sign or symbol representing) a unit that forms part of the system of counting and calculating:
examples: 25, 300, and a billion are all numbers.

definitions.definition: a number that is used to mark a particular example of something:
examples: They live at number 34 Orchard Street.

definitions.definition: to give something a number in a series and usually to write this number on it:
examples: All the folders have been carefully numbered and filed away.
